TY  - JOUR
T1  - Hub Arc Location Problems: Part II—Formulations and Optimal Algorithms
AU  - Campbell, J. F.
AU  - Ernst, A. T.
AU  - Krishnamoorthy, M.
Y1  - 2005/10/01
PY  - 2005
DA  - 2005/10/01
N1  - doi: 10.1287/mnsc.1050.0407
DO  - 10.1287/mnsc.1050.0407
T2  - Management Science
JF  - Management Science
JO  - Management Science
SP  - 1556
EP  - 1571
VL  - 51
IS  - 10
PB  - INFORMS
N2  - A companion paper (Campbell et al. 2005) introduces new hub arc location models and analyzes optimal solutions, with special attention to spatial pattens and relationships. This paper provides integer programming formulations and optimal solution algorithms for these problems. We describe two optimal solution approaches in detail and compare their performance, using standard hub location data sets. We present implementation details and show how algorithms can be fine tuned based on characteristics of the data.
AB  - A companion paper (Campbell et al. 2005) introduces new hub arc location models and analyzes optimal solutions, with special attention to spatial pattens and relationships. This paper provides integer programming formulations and optimal solution algorithms for these problems. We describe two optimal solution approaches in detail and compare their performance, using standard hub location data sets. We present implementation details and show how algorithms can be fine tuned based on characteristics of the data.
