T2  - Management Science
JF  - Management Science
JO  - Management Science
SP  - 1582
EP  - 1592
VL  - 51
IS  - 10
PB  - INFORMS
N2  - This paper makes indirect inference about the time variation in expected stock returns by comparing unconditional sample variances to estimates of expected conditional variances. The evidence reveals more predictability as more information is used, and there is no evidence that predictability has diminished in recent years. Semi-strong-form evidence suggests that time variation in expected returns remains economically important.
